The paper proposes a novel reinforcement learning approach for delayed rewards in finite Markov decision processes (MDPs) using reward redistribution and return decomposition via contribution analysis. This involves using deep learning for regression tasks and improving scores on Atari games with delayed rewards. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DL (Deep Learning). The paper also involves optimization and decision-making, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.GT (Game Theory).
